The paper focuses on unsupervised ranking from multi-attribute data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The proposed method uses principal curves to learn a one-dimensional manifold function for ranking, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
